  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the grill to high, then take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Top, tail and peel the<strong> mango<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></strong>, then stand the <strong>mango<span class=\"text-danger\">[es] </span></strong>upright and very carefully slice the flesh away from the stone<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> (if you feel resistance against your knife, it means you are hitting the stone)</p><p>Dice the <strong>mango flesh</strong> finely, discarding the stone<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></p><p>Zest 1/2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[1]</span> <strong>lime</strong> (try to grate lightly with a micro-plane or sharp box grater and avoid grating the white pith, as this is very bitter) and cut in half</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1684495789046-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1684495789046-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1684495789046-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1684495789046-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1684495789046-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> mango chutney </strong>to a large bowl with the<strong> ground turmeric</strong>,<strong> </strong>the juice of 1/2<span class=\"text-danger\"> [1]</span><strong> lime</strong>, a generous drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil </strong>and a generous pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Mix it all together – this is your <strong>mango & lime marinade</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>chicken thighs </strong>to the bowl with the marinade, mix it all together until fully coated and set aside for later – these are your <strong>marinated chicken thighs</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1684495800630-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1684495800630-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1684495800630-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1684495800630-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1684495800630-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>white long grain rice</strong> to a pot with a lid with 225ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[450ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once done, remove from the heat and set aside (lid on) to steam until serving</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1684495804430-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1684495804430-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1684495804430-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1684495804430-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1684495804430-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>marinated chicken thighs</strong> to a<strong> tin foil</strong>-lined baking tray (or two!)</p><p>Put the tray<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> under the grill for 15-20 min, turning once half way, or until cooked through (no pink meat!) and nicely charred – this is your <strong>mango & lime chicken</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1684495808278-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1684495808278-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
